Key Match Events: Stephen Curry scored 17 points in the third quarter, nearly outscoring the Thunder by himself in the fame
Jonathan Kuminga scored 12 points in the second quarter, helping the Warriors turn a seven-point deficit into a seven-point lead
Stephen Curry scored a season-high 36 points, surpassing his 27-point game against the Celtics
Post-Match Reflections: Draymond Green dished out a game-high 11 assists, generating 25 points for the Warriors
De'Anthony Melton had his highest scoring output as a Warrior, finishing with 19 points
Miscellaneous Highlights: Stephen Curry hit two clutch 3-pointers, the second followed by his signature 'night night' celebration
Chet Holmgren was injured early in the first quarter
The Warriors finished the difficult road trip with a 4-1 record
